1
00:00:00,918 --> 00:00:02,002
<i>- My name is Barry Allen,</i>

2
00:00:02,043 --> 00:00:04,254
<i>and I am
the fastest man alive.</i>

3
00:00:04,296 --> 00:00:05,506
<i>To the outside world,</i>

4
00:00:05,547 --> 00:00:07,424
<i>I'm an ordinary
forensic scientist.</i>

5
00:00:07,466 --> 00:00:09,050
<i>But secretly, with the help</i>

6
00:00:09,092 --> 00:00:10,845
<i>of my friends
at S.T.A.R. Labs,</i>

7
00:00:10,886 --> 00:00:12,346
<i>I fight crime
and find other meta-humans</i>

8
00:00:12,387 --> 00:00:13,597
<i>like me.</i>

9
00:00:13,639 --> 00:00:15,432
<i>But I became lost in time.</i>

10
00:00:15,474 --> 00:00:17,184
<i>It took everything
in my friends' power</i>

11
00:00:17,225 --> 00:00:19,227
<i>to bring me back,
and in doing so</i>

12
00:00:19,269 --> 00:00:21,647
<i>our world was opened up
to new threats.</i>

13
00:00:21,689 --> 00:00:24,023
<i>And I'm the only one
fast enough to stop them.</i>

14
00:00:24,065 --> 00:00:26,485
<i>I am the Flash.</i>

15
00:00:27,528 --> 00:00:29,488
<i>- Previously on "The Flash"...</i>

16
00:00:29,530 --> 00:00:31,573
- Is that what you think I am?
Some sort of evil secretary?

17
00:00:31,615 --> 00:00:33,241
- You tell me.
- I am now,

18
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:35,577
and forever will be,
my husband's partner.

19
00:00:35,619 --> 00:00:38,038
- Pleased to meet you,
Dominic Lanse.

20
00:00:38,079 --> 00:00:40,833
[yelling]

21
00:00:40,875 --> 00:00:42,209
- Hello, Mr. Allen.

22
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:44,336
- Devoe, if you
hurt my family...

23
00:00:44,378 --> 00:00:45,838
- I have no interest
in your family.

24
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:47,088
Besides, you're
gonna need someone

25
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:48,841
<i>to miss you when you're gone.</i>

26
00:00:48,883 --> 00:00:51,050
- What did you do?
- I left something for you.

27
00:00:51,092 --> 00:00:52,678
<i>I don't have need
for it anymore.</i>

28
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:54,137
- Barry Allen,
you're under arrest

29
00:00:54,179 --> 00:00:55,723
for the murder
of Clifford Devoe.

30
00:00:56,891 --> 00:00:58,767
<i>- My name is Barry Allen.</i>

31
00:00:58,809 --> 00:01:00,143
[camera shutter clicks]

32
00:01:00,185 --> 00:01:03,898
<i>And I'm an innocent man.</i>

33
00:01:03,939 --> 00:01:05,524
[camera shutter clicks]

34
00:01:05,566 --> 00:01:07,860
<i>I know that you'll find
my fingerprints</i>

35
00:01:07,902 --> 00:01:10,738
<i>all over his body.</i>

36
00:01:10,779 --> 00:01:14,533
<i>And I know that you'll find
his DNA on mine.</i>

37
00:01:14,575 --> 00:01:16,994
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

38
00:01:17,036 --> 00:01:21,373
<i>But I don't know
who stabbed him...</i>

39
00:01:21,415 --> 00:01:23,250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:25,335
<i>Or how he ended up in my loft.</i>

41
00:01:25,377 --> 00:01:27,922
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42
00:01:27,963 --> 00:01:30,591
<i>All I can tell you
is I'm being framed...</i>

43
00:01:30,632 --> 00:01:32,300
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44
00:01:32,342 --> 00:01:34,011
<i>For something I didn't do.</i>

45
00:01:34,053 --> 00:01:35,554
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46
00:01:35,596 --> 00:01:38,390
I didn't kill Clifford Devoe.

47
00:01:38,432 --> 00:01:39,808
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48
00:01:39,850 --> 00:01:41,018
- [sighs]

49
00:01:41,060 --> 00:01:46,147
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50
00:01:46,189 --> 00:01:48,233
All right, Allen,

51
00:01:48,275 --> 00:01:51,278
let's run it back
from the beginning.

52
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:53,072
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53
00:01:56,199 --> 00:01:57,868
<i>- This is exactly
what Devoe wanted.</i>

54
00:01:57,910 --> 00:02:01,622
I mean, we all played right
into his plan, especially me.

55
00:02:01,663 --> 00:02:03,498
- Why would Devoe want
to orchestrate all of this?

56
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:05,626
- I don't know,
but we know that this started

57
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:06,961
when I was still
in the Speed Force.

58
00:02:07,002 --> 00:02:08,670
- But why target Dominic?

59
00:02:08,712 --> 00:02:10,338
- Dominic's power must have
allowed Devoe

60
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:11,799
to inhabit his body.

61
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,550
We should've been
on top of this earlier.

62
00:02:13,592 --> 00:02:15,094
- What about
the other metas on the bus?

63
00:02:15,135 --> 00:02:17,387
Why create them?
- [sighs]

64
00:02:17,429 --> 00:02:19,473
Part of a larger plan?

65
00:02:19,514 --> 00:02:23,393
<i>[pensive music]</i>

66
00:02:23,435 --> 00:02:24,812
- How are you even here
right now, Allen?

67
00:02:24,853 --> 00:02:26,313
Aren't you on house arrest?

68
00:02:26,354 --> 00:02:27,731
- Yeah, well...
- He's at Joe's, actually.

69
00:02:27,773 --> 00:02:29,483
Either that
or the courthouse.

70
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:33,028
I managed to hack into
the ankle monitor GPS.

71
00:02:33,070 --> 00:02:35,155
- That's not
the only thing Cisco hacked.

72
00:02:35,196 --> 00:02:36,573
When you came
out of the Speed Force,

73
00:02:36,615 --> 00:02:38,366
you were talking
gibberish at CCPD.

74
00:02:38,408 --> 00:02:40,452
You said something about
not wanting to kill anyone.

75
00:02:40,494 --> 00:02:42,121
- I digitally scrubbed
a video.

76
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:43,664
Last thing we want
is somebody hearing something

77
00:02:43,705 --> 00:02:45,457
we don't want them to hear.

78
00:02:45,499 --> 00:02:48,877
- <i>Your Honor, I'm innocent.
I didn't do this.</i>

79
00:02:48,919 --> 00:02:50,587
<i>I didn't kill anyone.</i>

80
00:02:50,629 --> 00:02:52,840
Yeah, I mean, I don't remember
saying any of that.

81
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:54,925
- You don't?
- No.

82
00:02:54,967 --> 00:02:56,593
- We should look
at everything else he said

83
00:02:56,635 --> 00:02:58,303
when he first came out
of the Speed Force.

84
00:02:58,345 --> 00:02:59,554
Might give us a clue.
- That's a good idea.

85
00:02:59,596 --> 00:03:01,556
- Okay, guys,
but remember,

86
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:03,224
I mean, considering all the
evidence they have against me,

87
00:03:03,266 --> 00:03:05,060
this trial is not even
gonna last very long.

88
00:03:05,102 --> 00:03:07,104
- Okay, but with Cecile
taking a leave of absence

89
00:03:07,146 --> 00:03:09,564
to represent you, you got
the best lawyer in town.

90
00:03:09,606 --> 00:03:11,274
- Yeah,
- I mean, even if they did

91
00:03:11,316 --> 00:03:14,444
find you guilty, it's not like
any prison can hold you.

92
00:03:14,486 --> 00:03:17,990
- Well, I'm not gonna run.
I won't be a fugitive.

93
00:03:18,032 --> 00:03:20,075
If I'm convicted,
I have to go to prison.

94
00:03:20,117 --> 00:03:21,702
- We're not gonna let
that happen.

95
00:03:21,743 --> 00:03:23,328
<i>♪ ♪</i>

96
00:03:23,370 --> 00:03:26,205
- Right.
Let's get to work.

97
00:03:26,247 --> 00:03:31,837
<i>♪ ♪</i>

98
00:03:31,879 --> 00:03:33,338
- We should get
to the courthouse.

99
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:34,965
- Yeah.

100
00:03:35,007 --> 00:03:36,800
- How you doing?
- They say the first year

101
00:03:36,842 --> 00:03:38,510
of marriage
is always the hardest,

102
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:42,014
but I never thought my husband
being on trial for murder

103
00:03:42,056 --> 00:03:43,390
would be one of the challenges.

104
00:03:43,431 --> 00:03:45,433
- We have been through so much.

105
00:03:45,475 --> 00:03:47,728
We'll get through this too.

106
00:03:47,769 --> 00:03:49,521
- Will we, Barry?

107
00:03:49,563 --> 00:03:52,941
I know the Speed Force gave you
a new outlook on life, but...

108
00:03:52,983 --> 00:03:55,152
I don't know if being positive
is enough right now.

109
00:03:55,194 --> 00:03:58,906
- I'm just trying to be strong
for the team and for you.

110
00:03:58,947 --> 00:04:01,449
Remember, we're The Flash.

111
00:04:01,491 --> 00:04:03,410
<i>♪ ♪</i>

112
00:04:03,451 --> 00:04:05,829
- We're The Flash.

113
00:04:05,871 --> 00:04:07,455
- Ralph, hold up.

114
00:04:07,497 --> 00:04:09,499
Listen, I'm not gonna let
Barry go to prison.

115
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:10,792
I failed his dad,
I'm not gonna fail him.

116
00:04:10,834 --> 00:04:12,335
I need your help.

117
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:14,295
- My help, huh?
As in the stretchy kind?

118
00:04:14,337 --> 00:04:16,381
- As in the underhanded
private investigator kind.

119
00:04:16,423 --> 00:04:20,301
- Oh, ha, no offense taken.
- Come on.

120
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:24,389
- Science has long pondered
what would be required

121
00:04:24,431 --> 00:04:26,767
to successfully
transfer consciousness

122
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:30,604
from one living being
to another.

123
00:04:30,645 --> 00:04:32,397
But we've accomplished
far beyond

124
00:04:32,439 --> 00:04:35,234
a simple transfer
of consciousness.

125
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:38,112
We've extracted that
which elevates our humanity

126
00:04:38,153 --> 00:04:40,072
and added upon it.

127
00:04:40,114 --> 00:04:42,991
I am both who I was before...

128
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:45,160
- [inhales]

129
00:04:45,202 --> 00:04:48,622
- And who I desire to become.

130
00:04:48,663 --> 00:04:51,416
- Yes, you are, my love.

131
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:53,293
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

132
00:04:53,334 --> 00:04:56,379
- My hand still feels
foreign upon your flesh.

133
00:04:56,421 --> 00:04:58,381
<i>♪ ♪</i>

134
00:04:58,423 --> 00:05:00,759
And you don't care for it.

135
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:02,970
- No, I do.

136
00:05:03,011 --> 00:05:05,222
- As I said, I inherited
my host's ability

137
00:05:05,264 --> 00:05:07,182
to read thoughts.

138
00:05:08,809 --> 00:05:11,061
We have never lied
to each other before.

139
00:05:11,103 --> 00:05:13,855
Let's not begin now.

140
00:05:13,897 --> 00:05:15,523
- [whispers] Okay.

141
00:05:16,984 --> 00:05:20,612
- Marlize, my love...

142
00:05:22,322 --> 00:05:24,783
See past this body.

143
00:05:24,825 --> 00:05:27,327
See past these eyes.

144
00:05:29,079 --> 00:05:32,332
See me, Clifford.

145
00:05:32,373 --> 00:05:34,793
<i>♪ ♪</i>

146
00:05:34,835 --> 00:05:38,297
I am nothing without you.

147
00:05:38,337 --> 00:05:46,138
<i>♪ ♪</i>

148
00:05:51,434 --> 00:05:54,980
<i>- Your Honor, ladies
and gentleman of the jury,</i>

149
00:05:55,022 --> 00:05:57,607
For you to understand
what it is I'm about to tell you
today,

150
00:05:57,649 --> 00:05:59,234
you need to do something.

151
00:05:59,276 --> 00:06:03,238
I need you
to believe in the impossible.

152
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:05,406
As children, we're taught that

153
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:07,784
the police are there
to protect us, to serve.

154
00:06:07,826 --> 00:06:10,871
We're told that our tax dollars
go toward training them

155
00:06:10,912 --> 00:06:13,665
to be the champions
of the city.

156
00:06:13,707 --> 00:06:16,417
But for some of us,
it still seems impossible

157
00:06:16,459 --> 00:06:19,713
that a police investigator,
one of Central City's finest,

158
00:06:19,754 --> 00:06:21,506
could betray that trust.

159
00:06:21,548 --> 00:06:23,633
And even worse, under the guise
of upholding the law

160
00:06:23,675 --> 00:06:25,302
to commit the most heinous act

161
00:06:25,344 --> 00:06:27,304
that one person can carry out
against another.

162
00:06:27,346 --> 00:06:30,849
But that is exactly
what Barry Allen did.

163
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:33,727
Now, the prosecution
will prove beyond any doubt

164
00:06:33,768 --> 00:06:36,855
that he stood among us
a wolf in sheep's clothing.

165
00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:38,565
But here's the thing.

166
00:06:38,606 --> 00:06:40,734
Barry Allen wears a mask,

167
00:06:40,775 --> 00:06:43,362
used his connection
to the law,

168
00:06:43,402 --> 00:06:45,155
his experience
as a police investigator,

169
00:06:45,197 --> 00:06:47,490
especially as
a crime scene technician,

170
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:51,995
to stalk a beloved
professor and husband

171
00:06:52,037 --> 00:06:55,374
and murder Clifford Devoe
in cold blood.

172
00:06:55,414 --> 00:06:59,169
<i>[tense music]</i>

173
00:06:59,211 --> 00:07:01,088
- All right, Mr. Borwin,
just sign on the dotted line

174
00:07:01,129 --> 00:07:03,090
and your savings account
is all set up.

175
00:07:03,131 --> 00:07:05,342
- Appreciate your helping me
out, I want to get this right.

176
00:07:05,384 --> 00:07:07,552
It's my first savings account.

177
00:07:07,594 --> 00:07:10,013
<i>[eerie music]</i>

178
00:07:10,055 --> 00:07:12,182
You okay?
- Yeah.

179
00:07:12,224 --> 00:07:15,269
Just a little lightheaded
before lunch, I guess.

180
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:18,230
Have a great day.

181
00:07:18,272 --> 00:07:21,358
<i>♪ ♪</i>

182
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:25,404
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

183
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:27,948
<i>♪ ♪</i>

184
00:07:30,284 --> 00:07:33,120
- Ladies and gentleman,
the document in my hand,

185
00:07:33,161 --> 00:07:35,580
it's a court-issued
restraining order.

186
00:07:35,622 --> 00:07:37,624
It's issued to Marlize Devoe,
the wife of the victim,

187
00:07:37,665 --> 00:07:39,167
on behalf of her husband

188
00:07:39,209 --> 00:07:44,047
against a
Mr. Bartholomew Henry Allen.

189
00:07:44,089 --> 00:07:46,466
Now if you'd like a better
look, I have a bigger copy.

190
00:07:46,507 --> 00:07:48,093
And if you'll allow me
to call out

191
00:07:48,135 --> 00:07:50,804
what's written underneath
"reason for order issue,"

192
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:53,223
harassment.

193
00:07:53,265 --> 00:07:56,059
The defendant was seen
just days earlier,

194
00:07:56,101 --> 00:07:58,728
illegally breaking and entering
into the victim's house,

195
00:07:58,770 --> 00:08:00,730
searching through
the victim's effects.

196
00:08:00,772 --> 00:08:02,399
A man obsessed.

197
00:08:02,441 --> 00:08:04,401
Barry Allen's
skin cells were found

198
00:08:04,443 --> 00:08:07,528
under the nails of the victim.

199
00:08:07,570 --> 00:08:08,989
Now imagine that, if you can,

200
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:11,658
Mr. Devoe,
a man in a wheelchair,

201
00:08:11,699 --> 00:08:13,576
desperately trying
to defend himself

202
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:15,703
as Mr. Allen
sought to overpower him.

203
00:08:15,745 --> 00:08:17,831
And finally,
this is the knife

204
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:20,959
that was used
to kill Clifford Devoe.

205
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:26,340
If it looks new,
that's because it is.

206
00:08:26,381 --> 00:08:28,549
It was a wedding gift
to Mr. Allen.

207
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:31,928
Now let's just let that
sink in for a moment.

208
00:08:31,970 --> 00:08:33,596
This was supposed
to commemorate

209
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:36,266
the most joyous moment
in a couple's lives.

210
00:08:36,308 --> 00:08:37,976
But instead Mr. Allen used it

211
00:08:38,018 --> 00:08:40,812
to forever separate a couple
from one another.

212
00:08:40,854 --> 00:08:43,648
He used a wedding gift
as a murder weapon.

213
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:46,818
That is a special kind of evil.

214
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:48,403
[phone buzzing]
Defendant showed

215
00:08:48,445 --> 00:08:50,030
an absolute disregard...
- [whispers] Cisco,

216
00:08:50,071 --> 00:08:51,490
there's a meta attack downtown.

217
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:53,825
We got to go.
- Brazen callousness...

218
00:08:53,867 --> 00:08:57,496
- I'll stay here with Barry.

219
00:08:57,537 --> 00:09:00,623
<i>[tense music]</i>

220
00:09:00,665 --> 00:09:03,084
<i>♪ ♪</i>

221
00:09:03,126 --> 00:09:04,211
[siren wailing]

222
00:09:04,252 --> 00:09:05,545
Captain Singh:
When you're done here

223
00:09:05,586 --> 00:09:06,880
could I get some coverage
of the work stations?

224
00:09:06,921 --> 00:09:08,798
Detective, would you get
a statement please?

225
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:11,134
Mr. Ramon.
- Captain.

226
00:09:11,176 --> 00:09:13,720
- What happened here?
- Well, vintage Central City.

227
00:09:13,761 --> 00:09:15,514
Meaning another weird one.

228
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:19,851
No data breach, nothing stolen.
Everyone just collapsed.

229
00:09:19,893 --> 00:09:22,354
I have officers at the hospital
interviewing people now,

230
00:09:22,396 --> 00:09:24,022
but so far,
no one knows anything.

231
00:09:24,064 --> 00:09:25,399
- Hmm.
- Whoa.

232
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:27,484
[electronic beeping]
Dark matter city.

233
00:09:27,526 --> 00:09:29,444
Yeah, we're definitely
dealing with a meta here.

234
00:09:29,486 --> 00:09:31,571
- You want to see what kind of
perimeter we're dealing with?

235
00:09:31,612 --> 00:09:34,741
[fingers snap]
- You read my mind.

236
00:09:34,782 --> 00:09:37,618
- Hey, Joe, you sure you're
okay to run this case?

237
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:39,329
Because I totally understand

238
00:09:39,371 --> 00:09:41,540
if you need a little
more time, uh...

239
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:43,833
- Uh, I'm fine, really.

240
00:09:43,875 --> 00:09:46,294
I may have to go over
to the courthouse later.

241
00:09:46,336 --> 00:09:48,880
- Yeah, I'm, uh...
[clears throat]

242
00:09:48,922 --> 00:09:51,007
I'm actually heading
over there myself.

243
00:09:51,049 --> 00:09:52,467
[clears throat]

244
00:09:52,509 --> 00:09:54,886
The prosecution
called me to testify.

245
00:09:54,928 --> 00:09:56,555
I'm sorry, Joe.

246
00:09:56,596 --> 00:09:57,972
You know how much
I care about Barry,

247
00:09:58,014 --> 00:10:01,059
but I have to tell
them what I know.

