00:32:26,820 --> 00:32:28,614
- Do you think?

778
00:32:28,655 --> 00:32:30,407
- Wait, what if I create
a vacuum around him?

779
00:32:30,449 --> 00:32:31,825
That way,
even if he does explode,

780
00:32:31,867 --> 00:32:32,951
at least we contain the blast.

781
00:32:32,992 --> 00:32:34,536
<i>- Yeah, yes, Allen, yes.</i>

782
00:32:34,578 --> 00:32:36,162
That...that could work,
that could contain it.

783
00:32:36,204 --> 00:32:37,748
Whatever you're gonna do,
though, do it fast.

784
00:32:37,790 --> 00:32:40,375
<i>Fallout just went
above 8,000 rads.</i>

785
00:32:40,417 --> 00:32:43,587
[whooshing]

786
00:32:43,629 --> 00:32:44,880
- [yells]

787
00:32:44,922 --> 00:32:47,382
[grunting]

788
00:32:47,424 --> 00:32:49,259
<i>♪ ♪</i>

789
00:32:49,301 --> 00:32:51,136
- The vacuum's
containing his energy.

790
00:32:51,177 --> 00:32:52,763
<i>- Good.</i>

791
00:32:52,805 --> 00:32:54,848
- But he's still
getting stronger.

792
00:32:54,890 --> 00:32:56,349
<i>- Allen, I don't know long</i>

793
00:32:56,391 --> 00:32:58,268
<i>you can take
this much radiation.</i>

794
00:32:58,310 --> 00:33:00,270
- I don't have a choice.

795
00:33:00,312 --> 00:33:01,980
We have to contain his energy.

796
00:33:02,021 --> 00:33:04,065
- Allen, 9,000 rads.

797
00:33:04,107 --> 00:33:07,945
- [grunting]

798
00:33:07,986 --> 00:33:09,279
[beeping]

799
00:33:09,321 --> 00:33:10,948
- 10,000 rads, critical mass.

800
00:33:10,989 --> 00:33:12,783
Ramon, you need to send
that energy somewhere.

801
00:33:12,825 --> 00:33:14,159
- What? To where?

802
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:16,035
- Earth-15,
Earth-15 is a dead Earth.

803
00:33:16,077 --> 00:33:17,329
Breach it there now!

804
00:33:17,370 --> 00:33:21,416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

805
00:33:21,458 --> 00:33:26,171
- [yelling]

806
00:33:26,212 --> 00:33:30,550
<i>♪ ♪</i>

807
00:33:30,592 --> 00:33:32,761
[crackling]

808
00:33:32,803 --> 00:33:34,972
<i>♪ ♪</i>

809
00:33:35,013 --> 00:33:37,474
[yelling]

810
00:33:37,516 --> 00:33:40,853
[whooshing]

811
00:33:40,894 --> 00:33:48,318
<i>♪ ♪</i>

812
00:33:55,367 --> 00:33:58,578
- You did it.
Oh, man, you did it.

813
00:34:00,246 --> 00:34:01,999
You saved the day.

814
00:34:07,587 --> 00:34:09,756
<i>- Ladies and gentleman
of the jury,</i>

815
00:34:09,798 --> 00:34:11,508
you've reached a verdict?

816
00:34:11,550 --> 00:34:12,926
- We have, Your Honor.

817
00:34:12,968 --> 00:34:15,220
- All rise.

818
00:34:15,261 --> 00:34:17,848
<i>[tense music]</i>

819
00:34:17,890 --> 00:34:21,184
- For Docket Number 5677-B,

820
00:34:21,226 --> 00:34:25,397
in the matter of The People
vs. Bartholomew Henry Allen,

821
00:34:25,438 --> 00:34:27,900
we, the jury,
find the defendant

822
00:34:27,941 --> 00:34:30,736
