to neutralize him.

833
00:34:58,764 --> 00:35:00,390
<i>- Superior Court,
where minutes ago,</i>

834
00:35:00,432 --> 00:35:02,475
<i>the jury found
Bartholomew Henry Allen</i>

835
00:35:02,517 --> 00:35:04,978
<i>guilty in the murder
of Professor Clifford Devoe.</i>

836
00:35:05,020 --> 00:35:06,772
<i>Mr. Allen has been a CSI</i>

837
00:35:06,813 --> 00:35:08,065
<i>with the Central City
Police Department</i>

838
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:10,149
<i>for the last five years.</i>

839
00:35:10,191 --> 00:35:11,693
<i>In just a few short hours,</i>

840
00:35:11,735 --> 00:35:13,070
<i>the judge is expected
to announce</i>

841
00:35:13,111 --> 00:35:14,696
<i>Mr. Allen's sentence.</i>

842
00:35:14,738 --> 00:35:17,074
<i>Prosecutor Anton Slater
made a statement.</i>

843
00:35:17,115 --> 00:35:19,200
<i>He hoped Mr. Allen would
receive a life sentence,</i>

844
00:35:19,242 --> 00:35:21,494
<i>given the brutal nature
of the cri...</i>

845
00:35:21,536 --> 00:35:23,371
- I wanted to be
the one to tell you.

846
00:35:23,413 --> 00:35:25,373
- I can't believe
this is happening.

847
00:35:25,415 --> 00:35:28,794
- Come on, guys,
we just saved the city today.

848
00:35:28,835 --> 00:35:31,004
We knew this wasn't gonna go
my way in court.

849
00:35:31,046 --> 00:35:32,714
That doesn't mean
that Devoe beat us.

850
00:35:32,756 --> 00:35:34,674
- Whatever happens,
we're gonna keep fighting.

851
00:35:34,716 --> 00:35:36,635
- I know.

852
00:35:36,676 --> 00:35:38,053
- We need to get you back.

853
00:35:38,095 --> 00:35:39,972
You need to be there
for sentencing.

854
00:35:41,514 --> 00:35:42,849
- Yeah.

855
00:35:44,893 --> 00:35:47,520
- [sighs] I'll see you
guys later, all right?

856
00:35:49,022 --> 00:35:52,025
I'm gonna be okay,
all right?

857
00:35:52,067 --> 00:35:54,069
Come on.

858
00:35:54,111 --> 00:35:57,196
<i>[pensive music]</i>

859
00:35:57,238 --> 00:35:58,782
- You know
you got your strength

860
00:35:58,824 --> 00:36:01,159
from watching
your dad be your rock?

861
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:04,412
I got mine because...

862
00:36:04,454 --> 00:36:07,707
you're mine.

863
00:36:07,749 --> 00:36:09,668
I'll be strong for you.

864
00:36:09,709 --> 00:36:11,294
<i>♪ ♪</i>

865
00:36:11,336 --> 00:36:12,963
- I love you.

866
00:36:13,005 --> 00:36:15,298
- I love you.

867
00:36:15,340 --> 00:36:18,093
- Come on.

868
00:36:18,135 --> 00:36:19,469
[reporters clamoring]

869
00:36:19,511 --> 00:36:21,138
- Allen...
- Step back.

870
00:36:21,179 --> 00:36:25,391
[overlapping chatter]

871
00:36:25,433 --> 00:36:27,393
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

872
00:36:27,435 --> 00:36:29,646
- Yeah, I need a minute,
all right?

873
00:36:29,688 --> 00:36:32,649
[reporters shouting]

874
00:36:32,691 --> 00:36:36,028
- Mrs. Allen,
did you expect this?

875
00:36:36,069 --> 00:36:38,071
<i>♪ ♪</i>

876
00:36:38,113 --> 00:36:39,948
- Mr. Allen.

877
00:36:39,990 --> 00:36:42,034
<i>♪ ♪</i>

878
00:36:42,075 --> 00:36:43,827
- Devoe.

879
00:36:43,869 --> 00:36:45,662
- Did you know
there was a 12% chance

880
00:36:45,704 --> 00:36:48,456
that you were gonna tell
the world you're The Flash?

881
00:36:48,498 --> 00:36:50,583
- I'd recheck your math.

882
00:36:50,625 --> 00:36:52,669
- There's no need.

883
00:36:52,711 --> 00:36:54,921
Because no matter
what path you chose,

884
00:36:54,963 --> 00:36:57,049
all avenues led to my triumph.

885
00:36:57,090 --> 00:36:59,009
- Why do you
want us distracted?

886
00:36:59,051 --> 00:37:00,468
Why do you want me
out of the picture?

887
00:37:00,510 --> 00:37:02,095
What are you planning?

888
00:37:02,137 --> 00:37:04,014
- That you think
that you could understand

889
00:37:04,056 --> 00:37:08,060
the breadth of what I'm about
to do is almost humorous.

890
00:37:08,101 --> 00:37:10,020
- [exhales]

891
00:37:11,563 --> 00:37:16,068
- Yes, I think
you will miss Iris.

892
00:37:16,109 --> 00:37:17,694
That's right, Mr. Allen.

893
00:37:17,736 --> 00:37:20,030
I didn't just take
Dominic's body.

894
00:37:20,072 --> 00:37:22,866
I took his ability.

895
00:37:22,908 --> 00:37:25,535
I know what
you're thinking right now.

896
00:37:25,577 --> 00:37:28,997
<i>♪ ♪</i>

897
00:37:29,039 --> 00:37:32,000
- Well, I want you
to hear me say it.

898
00:37:32,042 --> 00:37:35,170
I'm gonna figure
a way out of this.

899
00:37:35,212 --> 00:37:36,880
And when I do,

900
00:37:36,922 --> 00:37:38,965
I don't care who's face
you're wearing.

901
00:37:39,007 --> 00:37:41,384
I'm coming for you.

902
00:37:41,426 --> 00:37:44,429
You haven't beaten us yet.

903
00:37:44,470 --> 00:37:46,639
- Haven't I?

904
00:37:46,681 --> 00:37:49,642
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

905
00:37:49,684 --> 00:37:52,145
<i>♪ ♪</i>

906
00:37:52,187 --> 00:37:54,731
Have a nice life, Mr. Allen.

907
00:37:54,773 --> 00:38:02,655
<i>♪ ♪</i>

908
00:38:09,204 --> 00:38:11,414
- Your Honor, I'm innocent.

909
00:38:11,456 --> 00:38:14,751
I didn't do this,
I didn't kill anyone.

910
00:38:14,793 --> 00:38:18,838
And I know that one day,
the truth will come out.

911
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:21,133
Thank you.

912
00:38:21,174 --> 00:38:23,384
- Rise for sentencing.

913
00:38:27,555 --> 00:38:30,100
In my 30 years
behind this bench,

914
00:38:30,142 --> 00:38:32,811
I have seen
my share of criminals.

915
00:38:32,852 --> 00:38:36,982
But I confess
this defendant stands apart.

916
00:38:37,023 --> 00:38:41,319
- Thank you all for coming
on such short notice.

917
00:38:41,360 --> 00:38:44,156
A few hours ago,
the very existence of our city

918
00:38:44,197 --> 00:38:47,075
came under the threat
of nuclear destruction.

919
00:38:47,117 --> 00:38:49,744
But one man rose
to meet that challenge.

920
00:38:49,786 --> 00:38:53,665
- The defendant was
in a position of authority.

921
00:38:53,706 --> 00:38:58,586
Our city trusted him
to bring the guilty to justice.

922
00:38:58,628 --> 00:39:00,713
- He ran into danger,

923
00:39:00,755 --> 00:39:03,466
knowing he would suffer burns
all over his body.

924
00:39:03,508 --> 00:39:07,137
- He used that trust to take an
innocent and vulnerable life.

925
00:39:07,179 --> 00:39:09,388
- This man was
not thinking about himself.

926
00:39:09,430 --> 00:39:11,016
He was thinking about you.

927
00:39:11,057 --> 00:39:13,268
The first responders
on the front lines.

928
00:39:13,310 --> 00:39:17,522
- Never have I seen
a defendant more unmoved.

929
00:39:17,563 --> 00:39:19,691
- Never have I seen
a man with more bravery.

930
00:39:19,732 --> 00:39:22,110
- Never have I seen
such inhumanity.

931
00:39:22,152 --> 00:39:23,736
- Such heroism.

932
00:39:23,778 --> 00:39:26,323
- Such a lack of regard
for human life.

933
00:39:26,364 --> 00:39:29,575
- It is my great honor
to present

934
00:39:29,617 --> 00:39:31,369
Central City
Police Department's

935
00:39:31,410 --> 00:39:32,954
Award of Valor

936
00:39:32,996 --> 00:39:35,373
to this city's finest hero.

937
00:39:35,414 --> 00:39:38,459
The fastest man alive,
The Flash!

938
00:39:38,501 --> 00:39:40,295
[applause]

939
00:39:40,337 --> 00:39:41,921
- The court hereby orders

940
00:39:41,963 --> 00:39:43,715
that Bartholomew Henry Allen

941
00:39:43,756 --> 00:39:45,342
should be incarcerated

942
00:39:45,383 --> 00:39:46,759
for the rest
of his natural life,

943
00:39:46,801 --> 00:39:49,679
without the possibility
of parole

944
00:39:49,721 --> 00:39:53,350
and that Mr. Allen
be immediately remanded

945
00:39:53,391 --> 00:39:56,144
to Iron Heights Penitentiary.

946
00:39:56,186 --> 00:39:59,314
And may God
have mercy on your soul.

